Unlike course homework problems which could be answered entirely with ChatBots with little to no additional prompting, the course project required significantly more prompts and “judgement calls”. One would need to ask Chat many, many questions to get desired code. Even when the code is provided, it is up to the individual to decide how that code is to be applied effectively to the project. 

This isn’t to say that ChatBots are not helpful! They are incredibly useful for accessing code which would have taken longer to create. For complex projects however, it is up to the individual to engage with Chat effectively.
I think chatGpt was a great resource and made my learning a lot “faster” instead of delaying any questions I would ask a human i could ask chatgpt and get an answer within seconds.

Since there were so many variables to choose a question from I had GPT go and analyze all the variables and help choose variables to study based on the question I had came up with. I however noticed that GPT would sometimes hallucinate variables that did not exist. Or GPT would correctly identify a variable that had data but the variable chosen was not interpreted correctly as in what GPT thought the variable recorded was not actually the question posted beside the variable name in the var_names.csv file
